snippet.textDisplay:
Gib did what I refer to as school yard boxing, he came in rushing with 10 oz gloves, I've always thought his fighting style was childlike in that respect. If you watch any school fight videos, most don't last longer than a minute or even less before someone buckles and buckling is enough to lose a fight per 3 knockdown rule. If he played tactical he might've had a chance. He refused to adapt or respect his opponent and kept auto pilot on, another aspect of his fighting style I find almost childish. It was a gambler's decision to not adapt, that was his downfall.

If he's a rusher, he should've picked his time to rush like an arrow or a sniper. If he's all about pressure, he should've relied on intimidation not the action, but he threw away that intimidation by continuously attacking. Combine these two tactics and I think he could've made a difference.
